00:00:16.070 --> 00:00:22.849
A Dutch design lab has conceptualized the
future highway. It features glow in the dark

00:00:22.849 --> 00:00:28.009
roads that charge during the day and light
up at night, asphalt paint that changes depending

00:00:28.009 --> 00:00:33.210
on the road conditions, such as snowflakes
when the roads are icy, and lanes that double

00:00:33.210 --> 00:00:38.649
as electric car chargers. Prototypes for the
asphalt paint and glow in the dark road are

00:00:38.649 --> 00:00:42.940
going to be implemented in 2013 on a stretch
of road in Holland.

00:00:42.940 --> 00:00:48.769
Meanwhile, in Japan, researchers are trying
to make car interiors appear transparent.

00:00:48.769 --> 00:00:54.760
The system applies optical camouflage technology
using video from rear cameras to project onto

00:00:54.760 --> 00:00:59.030
the backseat, and it's all processed by a
computer to make things appear actual-sized.

00:00:59.030 --> 00:01:04.780
Currently, only the backseat has been made
to look transparent, but the goal is to make

00:01:04.780 --> 00:01:10.200
the cars interior completely transparent in
order to eliminate blind spots.

